The Nigerian Basketball Federation (NBBF) has assured stakeholders that the federation is working round the clock to ensure the Premier League resumes soon. Speaking in Benin during the final of the basketball event of the on-going National Sports Festival, NBBF President, Musa Kida said the federation is “on the verge of concluding a deal with our sponsor. Once we strike a deal, the league will resume.” Kida said, “every one is eager to have the premier league back and for us, this is our focus. We have also informed the states’ associations and clubs to prepare for the Division Two and Division One Championships. Don’t forget Total Oil is our sponsor for these competitions.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .